---
const { organization } = Astro.props;
---

<section class="grid gap-4">
  <article class="card">
    <header>
      <h2>Profile summary</h2>
    </header>
    <section>
      <p class="leading-7 text-muted-foreground">
        This shared template renders both counties and municipalities from the same
        route shape. The page is ready for source-backed sections like contacts,
        services, budgets, or jobs as soon as those fields are wired in.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>

  <article class="card">
    <header>
      <h2>Data model check</h2>
    </header>
    <section>
      <p class="leading-7 text-muted-foreground">
        Organization type: <strong>{organization.organizationType}</strong>.
        The route does not change for cities versus counties; only the content
        branches when the data needs it.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</section>
